All nature speaks in silent words,   
E'er rustling through its myriad birds;   
A tapestry adorned in hues,   
In gentle sway, the love imbues.   
Through every glade, in moonlit glow,   
The earth shall share its truths and woe.

- Samuel Taylor Coleridge
